<br>
After debating over it for quite a while, Andrya sat up at the end of the bed.<br>
<br>
'Would he care if I...' she decided not to finish her thought as she shivered. <br>
<br>
Andrya made her decision, he wouldn't be that mad, she was really cold and he'd believe her, right? She made her way out of the guest room and into his.<br>
<br>
He was laying in his bed so peacefully, obviously not bothered by her not responding to him staying. She made her way around to the other side of the bed and quietly pulled back the covers. Her body slid into the bed with ease, and she hoped not to wake him up. Gently, she covered up and put her arm around him. Her body filled with warmth once her fingers met his skin.<br>
<br>
