<br>
As he walked in he saw the shirt he had let her use on the bed.  He slowly walked over to it and picked it up.  He held it in his hands for a minute, and felt something crumple inside of it.  He checked it and found a note.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;">Jacob,<br>
<br>
I loved last night.  I hope I can see you again.  When you get the chance, and you're not feeling too mad at me for leaving without waking you, give me a call.  My number's 555-6272<br>
<br>
Andrya</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
He looked at the note for a moment, before wadding it up and dropping it on the floor.  He thought she liked him, but he guessed she hadn't.  Slowly he walked out of the room, only to come running back in again at full speed.  He picked the piece of paper up as fast as he could, as if it was going to burn a hole through the very hull of the ship.  <br>
<br>
He opened it again, and straightened it out.  He neatly folded it up and placed it in his wallet, the number she had left facing up.  He would call her, but not until he had at least gotten out of the shower.  It had only taken him a second or two to realize that, she hadn't hurt him, but cared for him.<br>
