<br>
He ran to get ready, changing into his best clothes and brushing his hair.  He looked in the mirror before leaving, hoping that she liked how he looked.<br>
<br>
He went and got into his flyer.  He was excited about this, and hoped she would be too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#060C65><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bcollisionworld.showUserPublicProfile?gid=firestarter101>Fire Starter101</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#060C65>(2/17/03 11:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcollisionworldfrm189.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Jacob's Ship</span><hr size=1> Jacob smiled at her last comment.  He really liked being around her.  As they docked with the ship, he took her hand again and helped her out before taking her to the dining room.  It was different from the kitchen.  There was a table with an expensive white tablecloth on it.  There were candles on the table, and other candles around the room.<br>
<br>
Standing in the corner were two robots, each hold two trays.  The room itself was decorated with expensive tastes in mind, and the candles brought this out.  He brought her over to her chair and pulled it out for her politely before sitting down himself. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bcollisionworld.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xprettyxxgirl>xprettyxxgirl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#060C65>(2/17/03 11:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcollisionworldfrm189.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Jacob's Ship</span><hr size=1> Andrya sat down and glanced around the room. It was gorgeous. The robots scared her a little, but she tried not to let him notice. <br>
<br>
She thought about living in the future, and didn't think she could do it. Where there alot of people like her in the future? With the perfect body? Didn't genetics let parents make their kids perfect? So many questions, but she didn't want to bother him.<br>
<br>
She watched him take his seat. The candle light touched his skin and made him look like an angel. It was so beautiful. She wished she could have a picture of him like this.  <br>
<br>
Something crossed her mind, something that she had never even considered before. Being in a long-term relationship. He'd probably have a problem with her job, and her powers, and just her. She shrugged. No guy would ever want to be with her for a long time, they just wanted her until something new came along.<br>
<br>
&quot;Thanks for having me over&quot; she said, trying to smile. She hoped he didn't notice her sadness, and was sure that before the night was over, she'd be happy again. <p>--------<br>
