<br>
They were slim and harmless looking with a butlers bow-tie around their neck.  The trays they held had covers on them.  Each tray was a different size, one small and one medium.  They placed the small one down first, and another, shorter, arm came out of their torso to take the lid off.  Under was a bowl of soup.  They then placed the other down and lifted the lid off in the same manner.  This one was a steak with green beans.<br>
